      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The instantaneous aspect of entanglement can be eerie, but it's not supernatural – it's actually a result of the strange nature of quantum mechanics. According to Einstein's thought experiment, the \"spooky action at a distance,\" entangled particles can be instantaneously \"related\" because measurements in one particle can cause an \"information\" signal to be transmitted between them, not in the classical sense of physical signals, but more like a \"Battleham or transfer of states\". Think of it like when you drop two toy blocks from the same height at the same time - even if you can't see one from the other, you can still deduce their relative fate (both hitting the ground) because the force and motion are correlated from the start, before you take note.",
